## 1. Project Introduction
Title: Student Equipment Borrowing and Return Management System
Case Study: Built for a university or school to manage equipment borrowed by students (e.g., laptops, projectors, books). Purpose: The system replaces manual paper-based tracking of borrowed equipment with a reliable
online solution. It helps prevent loss, ensures accountability, and improves recordkeeping. Technologies Used:
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
Backend: PHP 8, MySQL
Tools: VS Code, XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)
## 2. Problem Statement
Problem: Many educational institutions face difficulties managing student equipment borrowing
manually. Equipment can get lost, double-booked, or records misplaced. Users:
Students: Borrow and return items
Admin: View, approve, and track all equipment activity
Features that solve the problem: - Digital forms for borrow and return
- Status tracking (pending, approved, returned) - Admin panel for review and update
- Availability tracking to avoid conflicts
## 3. System Requirements
Software: - Web browser (Chrome, Firefox) - Visual Studio Code (or any IDE) - XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)
(Optional) Hardware: - Windows PC or laptop
- 4GB+ RAM recommended
## 4. System Design
Navigation Flow:
Student → Register/Login → Dashboard → Request Item → Return Item
Admin → Login → View Requests → Mark as Returned
Pages: - Home (index.html) - Register (register.html) - Login (login.html) - Dashboard (dashboard.php) - Borrow form (borrow.php) - Return form (return.php) - Admin Panel (admin.php)
